  <Subject Subject_ID="300001955">
    <Parent_Relationships>
      <Preferred_Parent>
        <Parent_Subject_ID>300001954</Parent_Subject_ID>
        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>structures by location or context [300001954], structures (structural elements) [300000992], structural elements [300078048], structural elements and components for structural elements [300078046], architectural elements [300000885], components by specific context [300241584], components (objects parts) [300241583], Components (hierarchy name) [300241490], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Support systems and areas of buildings or other structures located below ground level or at the lower portions of structures when distinguishing these portions from the above ground or upper levels, in which case use "superstructures." Use "foundations (structural elements)" specifically for those parts of structures, usually below ground, that transmit loads to the supporting earth or rock.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wordt gebruikt voor de dragende systemen en gedeelten van gebouwen of andere constructies die zich ondergronds bevinden of in de lagere gedeelten van constructies, wanneer men deze delen wil onderscheiden van de bovengrondse of hogere gedeelten, waarvoor 'bovenbouw' wordt gebruikt. Gebruik 'funderingen' voor de specifieke delen van constructies, meestal ondergronds, die het gewicht overbrengen op de onderliggende aarde of rots.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079144/Haslinghuis, Bouwkundige termen (1986)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Sistemas de suporte e áreas de edifícios ou outras estruturas localizadas abaixo do nível do solo ou nas partes inferiores das estruturas ao distinguir essas partes dos níveis acima do solo ou superiores, caso em que use "superestruturas". Use "fundações (elementos estruturais)" especificamente para as partes das estruturas, geralmente abaixo do solo, que transmitem cargas para a terra ou rocha de suporte.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000316/CVAA-BR</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109633/CVAA-BR Consortium (2020-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
